00:49:01.190 --> 00:49:02.490
They're great but I
never heard of them.

00:49:02.490 --> 00:49:03.790
How did you find
out about them?"

00:49:03.790 --> 00:49:07.040
And he said, well, you
know, this -- the Internet.

00:49:07.040 --> 00:49:10.190
Their website's -- their
music's all over the Internet.

00:49:10.190 --> 00:49:14.590
So that was a new sort of -- to
me, that's sort of a new form

00:49:14.590 --> 00:49:19.520
of word of mouth, that sort of
spreads the word about artists

00:49:19.520 --> 00:49:22.830
that older people such as
myself don't know about.

00:49:22.830 --> 00:49:26.780
And to me that's a continuation
of the kind of folk music --

00:49:26.780 --> 00:49:28.750
the folk tradition that's there.

00:49:28.750 --> 00:49:31.300
Now, this is the 2009 festival.

00:49:31.300 --> 00:49:36.190
